<PB N="411" REF="425">
<HEAD>TITLES of the earlie&s;t BOOKS, and of the BIBLES
printed in the ROMANSH.</HEAD>
<P>N&deg; 1. <HI>The tran&s;lation of the New Te&s;tament by Biveronius.</HI> L'g Nuof Saint Te&s;ta|$aint
da no&s;s Signer Je&s;u Chri&s;ti Prais our delg Latin et our d' oters launguax et huo&s;&s;a da
noef mi&s;s in Arumaun&s;ch tr&eacute;s Jachiam Bi&s;run d' Agnedina. <HI>P&s;alm</HI> 119. Tieu uierf es una
glimyra a mes pes et una liu&s;th &agrave; micu pa&s;s. Squi&s;cho ilg an. 1560.</P>
<P>N&deg; 2. <HI>Another &s;carce work, printed by the &s;ame author in</HI> 1571, <HI>and which is in my
po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ion, containing a catechi&s;m and paraphra&s;e of the Lord's Prayer, in que&s;tion and an|&s;wer,
bears the following title.</HI> Una cuorta et fuorma da intraguidaer la giuvent&uuml;na et par 'lg
pr&uuml;m co es cugnio&s;che Deus et &s;e d'&s;ues. Alhura &uuml;na declaratiun de la Chredi$&s;ha, dals di&s;chs
cumandamains, dalg Poedernus, dals &s;ainchs &s;acramains, tuot tr&ecirc;s 'ls Preaichiauns da Chuoira
in moed da dumanda a&s;chant&ocirc;, et mi&s;&s;a in Aromaun&s;ch, 1571. <HI>From this book I &s;hall in&s;ert
the Apo&s;tles Creed, as a &s;pecimen of the early Roman&s;h.</HI></P>
<P>&startq;Eau craich in Dieu Paedar Omniputaint, creatur dalg t&s;chil et de la terra. Et in Je|&s;um
Chri&s;tum &s;es &s;ullet filg, nos Signur. L'g quael es concepieu dalg Sainch Spiert, na&s;chieu
da la Vergina Maria. Indur&ocirc; &s;uot Potio Pilato, crucifichi&ocirc; muort, et &s;appulieu. Jeu ad
ifiern, et aint ilg ters di da muort are&s;u&s;t&ocirc;. Et es jeu &agrave; t&s;chil, et &s;etza dalg dret maun da &s;es
bab cele&s;tiel. Innuonder che el vain &agrave; gnir &agrave; judichier vi&s;s et muorts. Eau craich aint ilg
&s;aine &s;piert. Eau craich che &s;aia la &s;ainchia fidela chri&s;tiauna ba&s;elgia. Comuniun dals
&s;enchs. Remi&s;ehiun dals pchios. Re&s;u&s;tatiun da la chiarn. Et &s;ieva aquai&s;ta vita, la vita
eterna. Amen.&endq;.</P>
<P>N&deg; 3. <HI>Title of Campel's tran&s;lation of the P&s;alms, &s;econd edition.</HI> Un Cude&s;cb Da
P&s;alms Tratts our da'gl Tudai&s;chk, e luguads da chiantar in Ladin. Proa quai alchiunas
Spiritualas Chiantzuns: chi s'ettuengen cun la vardad &egrave; &s;crittura &s;ainckgia, ed our da quella
tuutas, &amp;c. Tras Durich Chiampel, Sarviaint de l' g' Evangeli da Je&s;u Chri&s;ti a Su&s;ch
in Ingiadina $&s;uott. Schqui&s;chada a Ba&s;el 1606.</P>
<P>N&deg; 4. <HI>A Catechi&s;m by the Rev. John Planta, of Samada.</HI> Un Cuort Nuzaivel e B&s;og|nius
Catechi&s;mus, chi cuntain la &s;u&s;taunza da l'intyra Cretta, e vaira fae Chri&s;tiauna, &amp;c.
Scrit in Arumaunt&s;ch traes Juannem Plantam da Samedan, mini&s;tar de la Ba&s;elgia da Je&s;ui
Chri&s;ti. Squit&s;cho in Pu&s;chlaef traes Cornelium et Anthonium Landuolphs. 1581.</P>
<P>N&deg; 5. <HI>The Bible in the dialect of Lower Engadina.</HI> La &s;acra Biblia, quai ais Tuot la
Sonehia Scrittura in la quala &s;un comprais tuots Cuda&s;chs dal $elg e Nouf Te&s;tamaint cun
l'aggiunta dall Apocrypha e&s;chantada, vertida e &s;tampada in lingua Rumaun&s;$ha d' Ingadina
Ba&s;&s;a tras cumun cuo&s;t e lavear da Jacobo Antonio Vulpio, Serviaint dal Pled da Deis in
Ftaun, et Jacobo Dorta a Vulpera, Serviaint dal Pled da Deis in Scuol. Stampod in Seuol
in Ingadina Ba&s;&s;a tras Jacob Dorza a Vulpara. 1679. <HI>Fol. pag.</HI> 1524.</P>
<P>N&deg; 6. <HI>A ver&s;ion of the New Te&s;tament by John Gritti, and printed at Ba&s;le.</HI>
'L Nuof S. Te&s;tamaint da Nou&s;s Segnier Je&s;u Chri&s;ti huo&s;&s;a da n&ouml;f vertieu in Romaun&s;ch,
<PB N="412" REF="426">
our da l'originel Greec, traes Joann. da Zuoz, &amp;c. Squitcho in Ba&s;el traes George Decker,
&amp;c. 1640. 8<HI>vo. p.</HI> 870.</P>
<P>N&deg; 7. <HI>Aporta's Rhaetian Chronicle, printed at Scuol.</HI> Chronica Rhaetica order
l' Hi&s;toria da l'origine, guerras, alleanzas, et Auters evenimaints da no&s;&s;a chiara patria la
Rhetia, our da divers Authurs compomuda da Nott da Porta, V. D. M. et par bain public
acuo&s;t &s;eis fatta &s;tampar da Nuot N. Schucan tras Jacobo N. Gadina et Jac. Rauchio. In
Scuol. an. 1742. 8<HI>vo. p.</HI> 209.</P>
<P>N&deg; 8. <HI>The fir&s;t book in the Roman&s;h of the Grey League is a Catechi&s;m by Daniel
Boniface, under the following title: printed at Lindau.</HI> Catechi&s;mus, cu&s;t mu&s;&s;ameint dels
Principals Punctys della Chri&s;tianeita Religiun par las Ba&s;elgias et Skolas da Communas Trees
Ligias, tras quell ault amu&s;&s;aa S. Johann Ponti&s;ella da Cuira fatg per Tude&s;chk, u&s;&s;a da nief
tras Daniel Boniface me&s;s ora in Romaun&s;ch, &amp;c. Squitchau a Lindau vid igl Boden&s;ce tras
Johann Ludwig Brem. 1601. <HI>The following expre&s;&s;ions in his preface,</HI> &startq;et eint in no&s;s
linguagh mae na nean ne &s;critts ne &s;quitcheus;&endq; nothing having as yet appeared in our lan|guage,
either written or printed; <HI>&s;ufficiently proves that this Catechi&s;m was the fir&s;t pub|lication
in the Roman&s;h of the Grey League; although the following P&s;alter by Stephen
Gabriel, is u&s;ually &s;tyled the fir&s;t book.</HI></P>
<P>N&deg; 9. <HI>P&s;alter by Dan. Boniface, printed at Coire</HI> 1611; <HI>reprinted</HI> 1649, 1683, 1740,
1768. <HI>The following is the title-page of the la&s;t edition.</HI> Ilg Ver Sulaz da Pievel
Juven: quei anis una curta Summa da la Cardien&s;tha dils Patriarchs, Prophets, ad
Apo&s;tels: Item, Anzaquonts P&s;alms da David, a Canzuns Spiritualas: Item, Anzaquontas
Uratiuns: Tras Steffan Gabriel, &amp;c. Squitchau a Cuera. 1768.</P>
<P>N&deg; 10. <HI>Ver&s;ion of the New Te&s;tament by Lucius Gabriel, printed at Ba&s;le.</HI> Ilg
Nief Te&s;tament da Niefs Senger Je&s;u Chri&s;t me&s;s qui en Rumon&s;ch da la Liga Gri&s;cha tras
Luci Gabriel, &amp;c. Squitchau a Ba&s;el 1648. 8<HI>vo.</HI></P>
<P>N&deg; 11. <HI>Tran&s;lation of the Bible in the Roman&s;h of the Grey League, printed at
