<HEAD>N&deg; 3.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">ITINERARIES
OF
Four Tours through Switzerland, in 1776, 1779, 1785, and 1786;
With the Di&s;tances marked in leagues and Engli&s;h miles.</HEAD>
<P>IT may be nece&s;&s;ary to appri&s;e the traveller, that although I &s;pared no pains
in order to a&s;certain the re&s;pective di&s;tances, yet in many places, and parti|cularly
in the mountainous di&s;tricts, it was impo&s;&s;ible to obtain that degree of
accuracy which I could have de&s;ired. For in tho&s;e parts, the di&s;tances being
not mea&s;ured, can only be conjectured from the time employed in tra|ver&s;ing
them.</P>
